<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c0f83dd-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1484"><num value="1484">§ 1484.</num><heading> Interpretation and administration; other right, duty, privilege, or immunity and other remedy unaffected</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This chapter shall be interpreted and administered in a manner consistent with the convention, the protocol, and other international law. Except as specifically provided, nothing in this chapter may be interpreted to prejudice any otherwise applicable right, duty, privilege, or immunity or deprive any country or person of any remedy otherwise applicable.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c0f83de-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/93/248/s15">Pub. L. 93–248, § 15</ref>, <date date="1974-02-05">Feb. 5, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/10">88 Stat. 10</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/302/s1/6">Pub. L. 95–302, § 1(6)</ref>, <date date="1978-06-26">June 26, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/345">92 Stat. 345</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6c0f83df-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6c0f83e0-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id6c0f83e1-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1978—<ref href="/us/pl/95/302">Pub. L. 95–302</ref> inserted “, the protocol,” after “convention”.</p>
